⚔️ Aether Blade: Fragmented (Revised)
- Genre: Top-Down Action Rogue-lite
- Engine: Godot 4.4.1
- Platform: PC

🎮 Core Gameplay Loop
- Fight ➔ Loot ➔ Fight ➔ Upgrade ➔ Die ➔ Repeat

- Enter a room and defeat all enemies to progress.
- Collect Gold Coins and other in-run rewards.
- Spend Gold at intermittent shops for temporary boosts.
- After dying, receive Blue Mana Shards based on performance.
- Use Shards for permanent companion unlocks and Gold for permanent upgrades in the main menu before starting the next run.

🧙 The Player: The Blade Mage
- The Blade Mage wields both steel and arcane power, combining swift melee attacks with devastating magical abilities.
🗡️ Abilities
- Type	Name	Description	Cooldown / Cost
- Normal Attack	Just Slash	A standard melee attack.	None
- Skill 1	Aether Slash	A fast 3-hit melee combo. The third strike releases a magical crescent wave forward.	4 seconds
- Skill 2 (Special)	Blink Strike	Dash forward, turning invisible for 1 second and slashing all enemies in the path.	100 Energy
- Passive	Mana Overload	Every 5th hit causes the next attack to explode, dealing AoE damage.	Passive

🌀 Rogue-lite Mechanics
🏠 Room System
- Players progress through sequential combat rooms.
- Clearing all enemies unlocks the path to the next room and provides rewards.
- A Shop appears every 3 rooms, allowing players to spend Gold.

💰 Currencies & Economy
- Gold Coins: Dropped by defeated enemies and awarded for clearing rooms. Used to purchase temporary items and upgrades from the in-run Shop. Uncollected coins are automatically added to the player's inventory and can be used in the Main Menu Shop for permanent upgrades.
- Blue Mana Shards: A premium currency awarded to the player after a run ends. The amount is calculated based on the number of rooms cleared. Shards are used exclusively for the Companion Gacha System. This separation limits how many companions can be acquired per run, making it a strategic meta-progression choice.

🛒 In-Run Shop
(Accessed every 3 rooms, uses Gold Coins)
- Item	Effect
- Health Elixir	Restores 30% HP
- Sharpening Stone	+2 Base Damage (until death)
- Haste Potion	Increases attack speed by 10% (for the rest of the run)

🎰 Companion and Equipment Gacha System
- Currency: Blue Mana Shards
- Purpose: Summon permanent companions who provide passive buffs.
- Duplicate Summons: If a player summons a companion they already own, it will be converted into Companion Essence. This special resource is used to level up or enhance existing companions, unlocking improved stats or more powerful passive abilities (a "constellation" style system).

📈 Gacha System
- Game has a max pity of 70 pulls
- Companions and Equipment (5 stars) has a 1% chance of getting from 1-50 pity
- As the player pity reaches 51, the 1% chance will become 3.5% (1% + 2.5%), each 1 pull as the player reaches 51+ will add 2.5%
- Pull 70th is going to be the guaranteed banner highlight companion/equipment depending on where the player has pulled
- For every 10th pull = guaranteed 4 star, but when the player still not reaches 10 pulls, the chance of getting 4 star is 6%

List of 4 stars: (we will make it later on)
- 4x Large Health Potion (Type: Item)
- 2x Large Speed Potion (Type: Item)
- 2x Large Attack Buff (Type: Item)
- 2x Large Health Buff (Type: Item)
- 1x Massive Critrate Buff (Type: Item)
- 1x Massive Critdamage Buff (Type: Item)
- Random 1 Apprentice Equipment (Type: Equipment)

Apprentice Equipments consists of:
- Headgear
- Cloak
- Ring
- Shoes

🐉 Companion System
- Companions are permanent unlocks obtained through the Gacha system.
- Players can choose which companion to bring on a run.
- Each companion provides unique passive buffs that enhance the player’s combat effectiveness.
- Companions can be leveled up using Companion Essence.

👾 Enemy Variety (Palette Swap Technique)
- Enemy	Type	Description
- The Glitch	Melee	Fast with low HP. Uses the normal sprite.
- Void Caster	Ranged	Modulated purple. Stands still and fires magical orbs.
- Corrupted Guard	Tank	Scaled to 1.5× size, deep red modulation, and performs heavy attacks with screen shake.

📊 Stats
🧝 Player Stats (Level 1)
Stat	Value	Description
HP	100	Standard health pool
Base ATK	10	Damage per swing
Crit Rate	5%	Chance to deal critical damage
Crit DMG	150%	Critical damage multiplier
Move Speed	300	Pixels per second
Energy Max	100	Required for Special Skill
Energy/Hit	20	Energy gained per successful strike

👹 Enemy Stats (Level 1)
Stat	Value	Description
HP	30	Dies in 3 normal hits
Damage	10	Takes 10 hits to kill the player
Speed	200	Slower than the player

📈 Scaling Formulas
- Enemy HP Scaling: EnemyHP = BaseHP * (1.15 ^ (RoomNumber - 1))
- Player Damage Calculation: Damage = BaseATK * (1 + Sum of Bonus Percentages) + FlatBonus
- Blue Mana Shard Reward: Shards = floor(RoomsCleared / 2) + bonus (Example formula, can be refined)

🛡️ The "Wall" Strategy
- To prevent players from becoming overpowered and to test their build, Elite Enemies appear every 5 rooms.
- Elite Mechanics
  - 2× HP of a normal enemy for that room level.
  - Stun Shield: The shield must be hit 5 times before the enemy starts taking full damage. This forces players to engage strategically rather than relying on pure DPS.

🏛️ Development Approach (Godot)
- Since each character on the game no matter if player or enemy will have health, attack, movement speed, attack speed, crit rate, crit dmg, energy -  lets use a reusable component here that will allo us to import in each character and just edit the stats in the inspector for easier maintenance. 


Our Global Variables that we currently have:
1. PlayerInventory (it has the items, gold, shards, and equipments of the player)
2. PlayerStats (these are the stats of the player, health, attack, speed, critrate, critdamage (there might be missing))
